The article discusses the recent incident of gun violence in Sacramento, where six individuals were killed and several others injured. It expresses condolences to the victims and their families, and acknowledges that there are countless other victims of gun violence who do not receive national attention. The article emphasizes the need for action, stating that the administration has taken executive action to implement a comprehensive gun crime reduction strategy. It calls on Congress to ban ghost guns, require background checks for all gun sales, ban assault weapons and high-capacity magazines, repeal gun manufacturers' immunity from liability, and pass the budget proposal to provide more funding for police and crime prevention strategies. These measures are seen as urgent steps to save lives.